WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:06.677
Grey: WE LIVE OUT OUR LIVES
ON THE SURGICAL UNIT.

00:06.677 --> 00:11.312
7 DAYS A WEEK,
14 HOURS A DAY.

00:11.312 --> 00:14.215
WE'RE TOGETHER
MORE THAN WE'RE APART.

00:14.215 --> 00:15.516
AAH!

00:15.516 --> 00:17.318
GEORGE'S ROOM
IS BIGGER THAN MINE.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.092
[ SIGHS ]

00:21.092 --> 00:22.193
AUGH!

00:22.193 --> 00:23.524
AFTER A WHILE...

00:23.524 --> 00:26.057
I HAVE MORE CLOTHES --
I SHOULD HAVE THE BIGGER ROOM.

00:26.057 --> 00:27.428
...THE WAYS OF RESIDENCY...

00:27.428 --> 00:29.460
I GOT HERE FIRST.
MEREDITH SHOULD DECIDE.

00:29.460 --> 00:31.232
...BECOME THE WAYS OF LIFE.

00:31.232 --> 00:33.234
MY ROOM IS LIKE
TWO INCHES BIGGER.

00:33.234 --> 00:34.265
NUMBER ONE...

00:34.265 --> 00:36.137
YOU HAVE A BIGGER CLOSET.

00:36.137 --> 00:38.209
WHY IS EVERYTHING
A COMPETITION?

00:38.209 --> 00:39.810
ALWAYS KEEP SCORE.

00:43.043 --> 00:46.117
EVERYWHERE ELSE IS FILLED
WITH MEREDITH'S MOM'S BOXES.

00:46.117 --> 00:48.819
MEREDITH? WHEN IS YOUR MOM
COMING BACK TO TOWN, ANYWAY?

00:48.819 --> 00:51.322
BECAUSE MAYBE WE CAN PUT
HER BOXES IN STORAGE.

00:51.322 --> 00:54.125
OR UNPACK A FEW THINGS --
MAKE THIS PLACE MORE HOMEY.

00:54.125 --> 00:56.727
SOME THROW PILLOWS, SOME LAMPS,
A FEW PAINTINGS.

00:56.727 --> 00:58.389
OH,
PAINTINGS WOULD BE NICE.

00:58.389 --> 01:00.631
YOU HAVE ALL THIS
AMAZING STUFF PACKED AWAY.

01:00.631 --> 01:02.693
I FOUND THIS BOX
WITH TAPES OF YOUR MOTHER

01:02.693 --> 01:04.635
PERFORMING
AMAZING MEDICAL PROCEDURES.

01:04.635 --> 01:07.168
REALLY? WE SHOULD WATCH THEM.
DO YOU WANT TO WATCH --

01:13.104 --> 01:15.506
MEREDITH,
DO YOU WANT SOME PRIVACY?

01:15.506 --> 01:17.808
[ SIGHS ]

01:17.808 --> 01:21.182
NUMBER THREE -- DON'T MAKE
FRIENDS WITH THE ENEMY.

01:26.487 --> 01:28.319
MORNING, DR. BAILEY.

01:28.319 --> 01:29.320
SHUT UP.

01:29.320 --> 01:32.193
YOU REALIZE
THAT I'M AN ATTENDING

01:32.193 --> 01:35.766
AND YOU'RE ONLY A RESIDENT --
THAT YOU WORK FOR ME?

01:35.766 --> 01:38.129
I KNOW
I'VE FORGOTTEN SOMETHING.

01:38.129 --> 01:39.770
SOMETHING
IS HAPPENING TODAY.

01:39.770 --> 01:42.773
I KNOW I SHOULD KNOW
WHAT IT IS,

01:42.773 --> 01:44.535
BUT I JUST CAN'T...

01:45.606 --> 01:48.209
ALL RIGHT.
NICE TALKING WITH YOU.

01:48.209 --> 01:50.211
IT'S RIGHT IN FRONT
OF MY FACE.

01:50.211 --> 01:51.111
[ GASPS ]
WHOO-HOO!

01:51.111 --> 01:53.184
[ HORNS HONK ]

01:53.184 --> 01:54.145
WHOO!

01:54.145 --> 01:55.146
AUGH!

01:57.348 --> 01:58.549
[ HORNS HONK ]

02:00.221 --> 02:01.392
WATCH OUT.
WATCH OUT.

02:02.853 --> 02:03.894
OOH!

02:03.894 --> 02:05.396
WHOA!

02:05.396 --> 02:07.528
FOOLS ON BIKES,
KILLING THEMSELVES --

02:07.528 --> 02:09.430
NATURAL SELECTION
IS WHAT IT IS.

02:09.430 --> 02:12.263
SO WHAT'S UP WITH THE NAZI?
IS SHE OFF HER MEDS?

02:12.263 --> 02:13.804
YOU NEVER HEARD
OF THE RACE?

02:13.804 --> 02:17.738
EXCELLENT BOARD --
WELL-TIMED, BALANCED, EFFICIENT.

02:17.738 --> 02:20.341
IF ALL GOES WELL,
WE'LL HAVE AN EARLY NIGHT.

02:20.341 --> 02:23.214
CHIEF, "DEAD BABY" BIKE RACE
STARTED 20 MINUTES AGO.

02:23.214 --> 02:25.746
ALL RIGHT, PEOPLE!
DEAD BABY BIKE-RACE DAY!

02:25.746 --> 02:28.219
EVERY YEAR, THIS BAR --
THE DEAD BABY BAR.

02:28.219 --> 02:30.751
EVERY YEAR, THEY HOLD
THIS UNDERGROUND BIKE RACE.

02:30.751 --> 02:33.324
DON'T YOU WONDER WHY SOMEONE
WOULD NAME A BAR

02:33.324 --> 02:34.385
SOMETHING SO DISGUSTING?

02:34.385 --> 02:36.227
KEEP YOUR PANTIES ON,
NANCY DREW.

02:36.227 --> 02:38.589
THE RACE IS COMPLETELY ILLEGAL
AND --

02:38.589 --> 02:39.590
CRAZY.

02:39.590 --> 02:42.162
BIKE MESSENGERS
RACING AGAINST TRAFFIC,

02:42.162 --> 02:44.835
TRYING TO BEAT EACH OTHER
FOR FREE SHOTS OF TEQUILA.

02:44.835 --> 02:47.498
ALL-OUT, NO-HOLDS-BARRED
COMPETITION SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

02:47.498 --> 02:49.600
THE RACE DOESN'T EVEN
HAVE ANY RULES --

02:49.600 --> 02:51.602
EXCEPT EYE-GOUGING --
NO EYE-GOUGING.

02:51.602 --> 02:54.245
WE'RE GONNA BE TRAPPED
IN THE PIT BAND-AIDING IDIOTS

02:54.245 --> 02:55.506
WHEN WE COULD BE
UP IN THE O.R.

02:55.506 --> 02:58.749
WHAT KIND OF PEOPLE ENGAGE IN A
RACE THAT HAS, AS ITS ONLY RULE,

02:58.749 --> 03:01.812
THAT YOU CAN'T RIP OUT THE
EYEBALLS OF ANOTHER HUMAN BEING?

03:01.812 --> 03:03.314
MEN, GEORGIE.
MEN.

03:03.314 --> 03:05.616
I NEED SOMEONE TO GET UP
TO THE O.R. FLOOR.

03:05.616 --> 03:08.259
THE CHIEF NEEDS A RIGHT HAND.

03:08.259 --> 03:11.562
OH, AND YEAH, NUMBER FOUR...

03:11.562 --> 03:13.524
[ SIGHS ]
GEORGE.

03:13.524 --> 03:15.896
[ SIGHS ]
[ SIGHS ]
[ SIGHS ]
[ SIGHS ]

03:15.896 --> 03:17.428
...EVERYTHING IS A COMPETITION.

03:17.428 --> 03:19.400
OKAY, PEOPLE.
THE RULES OF TRAUMA --

03:19.400 --> 03:20.971
DON'T MINGLE
WITH E.R. INTERNS --

03:20.971 --> 03:22.873
THEY DON'T KNOW THEIR ASS
FROM THEIR ESOPHAGUS.

03:22.873 --> 03:26.237
SEW FAST, DISCHARGE FASTER.
GET BODIES UP TO THE O.R.

03:26.237 --> 03:29.310
AND DON'T LET ME CATCH YOU
FIGHTING OVER PATIENTS. GOT IT?

03:29.310 --> 03:30.541
COME ON.
LET'S GO.

03:35.786 --> 03:38.989
OH, IT'S LIKE CANDY,
BUT WITH BLOOD,

03:38.989 --> 03:40.991
WHICH IS SO MUCH BETTER!

03:40.991 --> 03:42.323
OH, MY GOD.

03:42.323 --> 03:43.324
MINE.

03:43.324 --> 03:45.326
NO!
I SAW HIM FIRST!

03:45.326 --> 03:47.458
WHOEVER SAID
WINNING WASN'T EVERYTHING...

03:47.458 --> 03:49.660
OOH.
I'LL TAKE THAT GUY.

03:49.660 --> 03:51.662
YOU'LL HAVE TO BEAT ME
TO HIM FIRST.

03:51.662 --> 03:54.265
...NEVER HELD A SCALPEL.

04:00.240 --> 04:03.914
