WHERE THEY MIGHT END UP â™ª

04:03.914 --> 04:06.847
â™ª NOBODY KNOWS â™ª

04:15.255 --> 04:17.257
â™ª OH, OH â™ª

04:17.257 --> 04:20.561
â™ª SUPPOSE YOU'LL NEVER KNOW â™ª

04:22.393 --> 04:24.335
HEADS -- HE'S MINE.
TAILS -- HE'S YOURS.

04:24.335 --> 04:25.696
WHY DO YOU GET
TO BE "HEADS"?

04:25.696 --> 04:28.339
BECAUSE I HAVE A HEAD,
AND, HONEY, YOU ARE A TAIL.

04:28.339 --> 04:29.340
EXCUSE ME.

04:29.340 --> 04:31.342
HOW DO YOU MANAGE
TO MAKE EVERYTHING DIRTY?

04:33.304 --> 04:35.346
HA! TAILS.
THERE ARE PLENTY OF OTHER CASES.

04:35.346 --> 04:37.308
SO GO GET ONE.
I WAS HERE FIRST.

04:37.308 --> 04:39.710
I AM NOT BACKING DOWN
SO I CAN DO SUTURES ALL DAY,

04:39.710 --> 04:41.281
WHILE YOU'RE IN THE O.R.

04:41.281 --> 04:43.454
THIS IS A SURGICAL CASE,
AND YOU KNOW IT.

04:43.454 --> 04:45.816
IT'S SUPERFICIAL.
IT'S COOL, BUT IT'S SUPERFICIAL.

04:45.816 --> 04:48.759
HOW DO YOU KNOW THOSE THINGS
DIDN'T RUPTURE HIS PERITONEUM?

04:48.759 --> 04:51.392
BECAUSE HE'S SITTING UP,
AND HE'S TALKING TO US.

04:51.392 --> 04:52.593
HELLO.

04:52.593 --> 04:55.326
I WAS WONDERING IF YOU COULD
TAKE THESE OUT AND SEW ME UP

04:55.326 --> 04:56.867
SO I COULD GO
AND WIN MY RACE.

04:56.867 --> 04:59.570
WELL, WE CAN'T
JUST PULL THEM OUT --
[ GRUNTS ]

04:59.570 --> 05:01.932
WE HAVE TO...
DO SOME TESTS
OW, WICKED.

05:01.932 --> 05:04.605
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

05:04.605 --> 05:06.477
IT'S A SUPERFICIAL WOUND.

05:06.477 --> 05:09.410
SEW HIM UP
AND LET HIM FINISH HIS RACE.

05:09.410 --> 05:11.482
HEY, GOOD MAN.

05:11.482 --> 05:13.784
UNIDENTIFIED JOHN DOE,
MID-30s PEDESTRIAN,

05:13.784 --> 05:16.316
HIT BY A MOTORIST
SWERVING TO AVOID A BIKE.

05:16.316 --> 05:18.489
G.C.S. 3.
PUPILS FIXED AND DILATED.

05:18.489 --> 05:21.392
ATROPINE GIVEN
FOR A PULSE IN THE 40s.

05:21.392 --> 05:23.524
B.P. 183 OVER 112.
PULSE-OX 98%.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.526
CHEST SHOWED
WIDENED MEDIASTINUM

05:25.526 --> 05:27.758
AND HEAD C.T. REVEALED
CEREBRAL EDEMA.

05:27.758 --> 05:30.401
HE'S GOTTEN 70 OF MANNITOL,
DEXAMETHASONE 10,

05:30.401 --> 05:31.802
AND A GRAM OF PHENYTOIN.

05:31.802 --> 05:32.803
GET HIM TO THE O.R.?

05:32.803 --> 05:34.835
IS HE GORKED?
LOOKS LIKE.

05:34.835 --> 05:38.338
THE BIKE RACE CLAIMS
ITS FIRST VICTIM.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.671
I'LL MAKE MY TRIPLE-A REPAIR
AFTER ALL.

05:40.671 --> 05:44.445
UH, DR. SHEPHERD?
HE'S NOT GOING TO THE O.R.?

05:44.445 --> 05:47.818
NO. DO AN E.E.G.
AND CONFIRMATORY TESTS.

05:47.818 --> 05:51.952
IF HE DOESN'T RESPOND
IN SIX HOURS, DECLARE HIM.

05:54.024 --> 05:56.457
"DECLARE HIM"?
DECLARE HIM WHAT?

05:56.457 --> 05:57.528
BRAIN-DEAD.

05:59.430 --> 06:00.761
[ SIGHS ]

06:05.666 --> 06:08.599
SIR, DR. BAILEY SENT ME.
SHOULD I SCRUB IN?

06:08.599 --> 06:10.671
NO.
I'M STUCK HERE ALL DAY.

06:10.671 --> 06:12.503
I NEED YOU ON THE FLOOR,

06:12.503 --> 06:15.976
MONITORING
MY PRE- AND POST-OP PATIENTS.

06:15.976 --> 06:17.007
OH.

06:17.007 --> 06:19.109
YOU GOT A PROBLEM WITH THAT,
O'MALLEY?

06:19.109 --> 06:22.483
OH, UH, NO, SIR.

06:22.483 --> 06:25.556
A BUDDY OF MINE IN 4451,
LLOYD MACKIE --

06:25.556 --> 06:28.689
GIVE HIM WHATEVER HE NEEDS.

06:28.689 --> 06:30.561
YES, SIR.

06:44.935 --> 06:46.807
O'Malley:
MR. MACKIE...

06:46.807 --> 06:48.679
NO SMOKING!

06:48.679 --> 06:50.541
THERE'S NO SMOKING.

06:50.541 --> 06:51.542
WHY NOT?

06:51.542 --> 06:54.545
OH, MY GOD --
YOU'RE IN A HOSPITAL!

06:54.545 --> 06:55.415
YOUR POINT BEING...?

06:57.448 --> 07:00.691
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'VE LISTENED
TO THE SURGEON GENERAL LATELY --

07:00.691 --> 07:02.623
SAY,
IN THE PAST 20 YEARS --

07:02.623 --> 07:04.555
BUT SMOKING IS BAD.

07:04.555 --> 07:05.726
SMOKING WILL KILL YOU.

07:05.726 --> 07:07.998
LIVER CANCER WILL KILL ME.

07:07.998 --> 07:11.602
SMOKING WILL JUST SPEED UP
THE PROCESS.

07:11.602 --> 07:15.466
YOU'RE AT THE TOP OF
THE DONOR LIST FOR A NEW LIVER.

07:15.466 --> 07:16.567
THERE'S HOPE.

07:16.567 --> 07:21.441
SWEETHEART, I'VE BEEN AT
THE TOP OF THE LIST FOR...

07:21.441 --> 07:22.643
EIGHT MONTHS.

07:22.643 --> 07:25.075
I'M NOT IN A BATTERS CAGE.

07:25.075 --> 07:28.579
I'M IN A DUGOUT,
ABOUT TO BE TRADED.

07:28.579 --> 07:31.121
YOU LIKE BASEBALL?

07:31.121 --> 07:32.823
NO.

07:32.823 --> 07:34.084
OH.

07:34.084 --> 07:37.988
UM, WELL, UM, THE CHIEF
WANTED ME TO LOOK IN ON YOU.

07:37.988 --> 07:38.989
HMM.

07:38.989 --> 07:41.592
RICHARD'S A DEAR OLD FRIEND.

07:41.592 --> 07:44.935
HE'S BEEN MY DOCTOR
FOR 30 YEARS.

07:44.935 --> 07:48.599
WELL, WHATEVER YOU NEED --
I'M YOUR MAN.

07:48.599 --> 07:49.740
JUST NAME IT.

07:49.740 --> 07:53.143
WELL...

07:53.143 --> 07:55.746
I'M SURE I'LL THINK
OF SOMETHING.

08:06.056 --> 08:09.520
ABSENT CORNEAL REFLEXES.

08:09.520 --> 08:12.693
IT'S BEEN 55 MINUTES.

08:12.693 --> 08:15.566
IF HE DOESN'T RESPOND TO TESTS
IN THE NEXT FIVE HOURS, WHAT?

08:15.566 --> 08:18.498
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO JUST
STAND HERE AND WATCH HIM DIE?

08:18.498 --> 08:20.531
IF HE DOESN'T RESPOND
TO THESE TESTS,

08:20.531 --> 08:22.703
IT'S BECAUSE
HE'S ALREADY DEAD.

08:22.703 --> 08:24.835
[ SCOFFS ]
TECHNICALLY. LEGALLY.

08:24.835 --> 08:26.977
ACTUALLY, IZZIE.
ACTUALLY DEAD.

08:26.977 --> 08:28.739
HE'S BREATHING.
HE HAS A HEARTBEAT.

08:28.739 --> 08:31.612
LOOK AT HIS E.E.G. -- THERE'S
NO HIGHER-BRAIN FUNCTION.

08:31.612 --> 08:33.884
HE'LL NEVER TALK, MOVE,
OR THINK AGAIN.

08:33.884 --> 08:36.747
THERE'S NO ONE IN THERE.
THINK LIKE A DOCTOR, IZZIE.

08:36.747 --> 08:38.619
HE COULD WAKE UP.

08:38.619 --> 08:40.591
WHAT ABOUT A MIRACLE?

08:40.591 --> 08:42.923
THERE ARE MEDICAL MIRACLES,
YOU KNOW.

08:42.923 --> 08:45.726
I KNOW. YOU'RE RIGHT.
MIRACLES HAPPEN.

08:45.726 --> 08:48.028
THAT'S WHY WE DO
A SERIES OF TESTS

08:48.028 --> 08:49.900
OVER A SET NUMBER
OF HOURS.

08:49.900 --> 08:52.262
SO WHEN WE CALL
"TIME OF DEATH,"

08:52.262 --> 08:55.736
WE KNOW THAT WE'VE
DONE EVERYTHING TO MAKE SURE

08:55.736 --> 08:57.537
IT'S ACTUALLY
HIS TIME OF DEATH,

08:57.537 --> 09:00.771
THAT THERE'S ISN'T GOING TO BE
ANY MIRACLES.

09:03.614 --> 09:05.816
THIS IS THE HARD PART --

09:05.816 --> 09:09.119
TO STAND AROUND AS SURGEONS
AND NOT CUT.

09:09.119 --> 09:12.282
THAT'S WHAT
"DO NO HARM" MEANS.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.888
I WISH HE'D JUST
GO INTO THE LIGHT

09:17.888 --> 09:19.730
SO I CAN GET
ON ANOTHER CASE.

09:22.192 --> 09:24.835
OH, I'M THE DEVIL
BECAUSE I'D RATHER BE IN SURGERY

09:24.835 --> 09:27.668
INSTEAD OF STANDING WATCH
OVER THE DEATH SQUAD?

09:27.668 --> 09:28.939
IT'S DEPRESSING.

09:33.644 --> 09:37.577
LOOK AT HIS SNEAKERS.
THEY'RE BRAND-NEW.

09:37.577 --> 09:39.910
AND SOMEBODY SEWED THIS TEAR
IN HIS SHIRT.

09:39.910 --> 09:42.653
AND HE HAS ONE OF THOSE
ELECTRONIC KEY CARDS.

09:42.653 --> 09:43.984
HE BELONGS TO SOMEONE.

09:43.984 --> 09:46.617
AN HOUR AGO,
HE WAS OUT THERE, ALIVE.

09:46.617 --> 09:49.820
TO SIMPLY STAND HERE
AND WAIT FOR HIM TO DIE --

09:49.820 --> 09:51.962
IT WOULD BE
A WASTE OF LIFE.
EXACTLY.

09:51.962 --> 09:53.664
A WASTE OF ORGANS.

10:01.071 --> 10:04.204
AHH.
YOU'VE GOT A NICE TOUCH.

10:04.204 --> 10:07.007
[ SIGHS ] AND, BY THE WAY,
YOU ARE A ROCKIN' BABE.

10:07.007 --> 10:10.140
SERIOUSLY -- DO YOU ACTUALLY
THINK YOU HAVE A SHOT HERE?

10:10.140 --> 10:12.813
I'D LIKE TO THINK
I'VE GOT A SHOT ANYWHERE.

10:12.813 --> 10:13.984
HMM.

10:13.984 --> 10:17.187
LOOK, YOU HAVE REALLY HAVE TO
LET ME TAKE YOU FOR SOME TESTS.

10:17.187 --> 10:19.119
YOU COULD HAVE
INTERNAL BLEEDING.

10:19.119 --> 10:21.652
NO, THANK YOU.
I'VE GOT A RACE TO GET BACK TO.

10:21.652 --> 10:23.654
WHY?
YOU CAN'T WIN NOW, ANYWAY.

10:23.654 --> 10:26.296
DOESN'T MEAN I CAN'T CROSS
THAT FINISH LINE.

10:26.296 --> 10:28.699
THERE'S A PARTY
AT THE FINISH LINE.

10:28.699 --> 10:30.701
Do you want
to meet me there?

10:30.701 --> 10:33.834
ONE TEST. I'LL HAVE YOU
OUT OF HERE IN AN HOUR.

10:33.834 --> 10:35.966
I CAN'T DO IT.
GOT TO GO.

10:35.966 --> 10:37.838
EHH.

10:37.838 --> 10:40.841
WELL, YOU REALIZE YOU'RE LEAVING
AGAINST MEDICAL ADVICE

10:40.841 --> 10:42.773
AND THAT I URGE YOU
TO STAY.

10:42.773 --> 10:44.715
THE FRAT GUY SAID
I COULD GO.

10:44.715 --> 10:47.217
THE "FRAT GUY" IS AN ASS.

10:47.217 --> 10:51.782
OKAY, WELL,
YOU HAVE TO SIGN AN A.M.A. FORM.

10:51.782 --> 10:54.985
DARLING, I WILL DO ANYTHING
YOU WANT ME TO.

10:54.985 --> 10:56.887
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU GUYS

10:56.887 --> 10:59.930
AND YOUR NEED
TO DIRTY EVERYTHING UP?

10:59.930 --> 11:03.393
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE IT'S JUST TESTOSTERONE.

11:03.393 --> 11:04.735
MAYBE.

11:04.735 --> 11:07.868
YOU MIGHT WANT TO SEE
A DOCTOR ABOUT THAT, TOO.

11:07.868 --> 11:09.139
COME HERE.

11:10.741 --> 11:12.402
[ SIGHS ]

11:21.111 --> 11:22.813
THAT WAS FOR GOOD LUCK.

11:22.813 --> 11:26.757
DON'T WORRY, DARLING,
YOU'LL SEE ME AGAIN.

11:26.757 --> 11:28.989
FOR YOUR SAKE, I HOPE NOT.

11:28.989 --> 11:30.360
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

11:33.293 --> 11:34.294
[ SIGHS ]

11:42.773 --> 11:43.904
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

11:43.904 --> 11:46.176
YOU MAKE OUT
WITH PATIENTS NOW?

11:46.176 --> 11:48.178
WHAT, ARE YOU JEALOUS?

11:48.178 --> 11:50.841
I DON'T GET JEALOUS.

11:52.883 --> 11:55.916
WE HAD SEX -- ONCE.

11:55.916 --> 11:58.488
AND WE KISSED
IN AN ELEVATOR.

11:58.488 --> 12:01.051
AND WE KISSED
IN AN ELEVATOR -- ONCE.

12:01.051 --> 12:02.893
NO, SERIOUSLY.
GO OUT WITH ME.

12:02.893 --> 12:03.894
NO.

12:03.894 --> 12:05.826
YOU KNOW,
I ALMOST DIED TODAY.

12:05.826 --> 12:07.898
YEAH,
I CAME LIKE THIS CLOSE.

12:07.898 --> 12:09.499
HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
IF I DIED

12:09.499 --> 12:12.262
AND YOU DIDN'T GET A CHANCE
TO GO OUT WITH ME?

12:12.262 --> 12:14.765
GET OVER YOURSELF, ALREADY.

12:14.765 --> 12:15.936
COME ON.

12:15.936 --> 12:19.109
IT'S THE CHASE, ISN'T IT?

12:19.109 --> 12:20.170
WHAT?

12:20.170 --> 12:21.741
THE THRILL OF THE CHASE.

12:21.741 --> 12:23.173
I'VE BEEN WONDERING
TO MYSELF,

12:23.173 --> 12:26.416
"WHY ARE YOU SO HELL-BENT ON
GETTING ME TO GO OUT WITH YOU?"

12:26.416 --> 12:27.848
YOU KNOW YOU'RE MY BOSS,

12:27.848 --> 12:29.780
YOU KNOW
IT'S AGAINST THE RULES,

12:29.780 --> 12:32.152
YOU KNOW I KEEP SAYING NO --
IT'S THE CHASE.

12:32.152 --> 12:34.054
WELL, IT'S FUN, ISN'T IT?

12:34.054 --> 12:36.827
YOU SEE?
THIS IS A GAME TO YOU.

12:36.827 --> 12:37.888
BUT NOT TO ME.

12:37.888 --> 12:41.962
BECAUSE, UNLIKE YOU,
I STILL HAVE SOMETHING TO PROVE.

12:43.834 --> 12:46.336
I KNOW YOU SEE ME RESECTING
THIS BOWEL.

12:46.336 --> 12:49.970
DO I STRIKE YOU AS SOMEONE
WHO ENJOYS MULTITASKING?

12:49.970 --> 12:52.873
WE HAVE A JOHN DOE. IN THREE
HOURS, WE HAVE TO DECLARE HIM.

12:52.873 --> 12:54.875
WE WANT TO HARVEST
HIS ORGANS.

12:54.875 --> 12:56.306
WHY ARE YOU WASTING TIME
ON THIS?

12:56.306 --> 12:58.448
YOU KNOW HOW MANY PATIENTS
WE HAVE DOWNSTAIRS.

12:58.448 --> 13:01.151
IF HE DIES --
AND HE COULD STILL LIVE --

13:01.151 --> 13:03.383
HIS DEATH SHOULD
MEAN SOMETHING.

13:03.383 --> 13:06.957
AND YOU WANT
A HARVEST SURGERY.

13:06.957 --> 13:08.819
I WANT TO SAVE LIVES.

13:10.861 --> 13:12.893
OKAY,
I WANT A HARVEST SURGERY.

13:12.893 --> 13:14.965
GETTING ORGANS FROM A JOHN DOE
IS A LONG SHOT.

13:14.965 --> 13:17.197
WITHOUT I.D.,
YOU CAN'T CONTACT THE FAMILY.

13:17.197 --> 13:19.870
WITHOUT THE FAMILY,
YOU CAN'T GET CONSENT.

13:19.870 --> 13:21.531
LET THE POOR MAN DIE
IN PEACE.

13:21.531 --> 13:23.333
WHAT IF WE CAN FIND
THE FAMILY?

13:23.333 --> 13:24.334
AND GET CONSENT.

13:24.334 --> 13:26.036
WE COULD HARVEST
THE ORGANS?

13:26.036 --> 13:28.238
IF YOU FIND THE FAMILY.

13:33.884 --> 13:35.916
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

13:35.916 --> 13:36.917
HIDING.

13:36.917 --> 13:39.149
THERE'S THIS
V.I.P. PATIENT --

13:39.149 --> 13:40.420
HE LIKES ME.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.092
THAT'S GOOD, RIGHT?

13:42.092 --> 13:44.895
HE LIKES ME LIKES ME.

13:44.895 --> 13:48.498
GO FOR IT, MAN. GET YOURS.
I'M DOWN WITH THE RAINBOW.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.506
OH.
ARE YOU NOT GAY?

13:56.506 --> 13:57.968
NO.

13:57.968 --> 13:59.469
REALLY?

13:59.469 --> 14:01.942
DUDE, SORRY.

14:06.947 --> 14:08.879
UH, CRISTINA?

14:10.921 --> 14:12.983
DO YOU --
DO YOU THINK --

14:12.983 --> 14:15.225
DOES MEREDITH
THINK I'M GAY?

14:15.225 --> 14:16.957
ARE YOU?

14:16.957 --> 14:18.358
No.

14:18.358 --> 14:19.459
REALLY?

14:23.063 --> 14:25.936
Stevens: HEY,
I FOUND THIS ON OUR JOHN DOE.

14:25.936 --> 14:27.237
IT'S A HOTEL KEY CARD.

14:27.237 --> 14:29.639
THE POLICE ARE GOING TO SEND
SOMEONE OVER,

14:29.639 --> 14:32.872
FIGURE OUT WHAT HOTEL HE WAS
STAYING AT -- GET HIS I.D.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.044
I'LL MAKE SURE
THE POLICE GET IT.

14:34.044 --> 14:35.645
OKAY.
IT'S REALLY IMPORTANT.

14:35.645 --> 14:38.448
WE ONLY HAVE A FEW HOURS
BEFORE WE HAVE TO DECLARE HIM,

14:38.448 --> 14:40.510
AND I'D REALLY LIKE
TO FIND HIS FAMILY.

14:40.510 --> 14:43.113
YOU WANT THEIR PERMISSION
FOR ORGAN DONATION?

14:45.655 --> 14:48.258
I JUST...REALLY WANT
TO FIND THEM.

14:50.260 --> 14:52.092
YOU HAVE A POTENTIAL DONOR?

14:53.423 --> 14:54.624
WHAT'S HIS BLOOD TYPE?

14:54.624 --> 14:56.366
UH, O-NEG.

15:07.537 --> 15:08.578
OKAY.

15:08.578 --> 15:11.041
I KNOW YOU PROBABLY
CAN'T HEAR ME

15:11.041 --> 15:14.985
AND YOU'RE FEELING THIS BIG PUSH
TO GO TOWARDS THE LIGHT,

15:14.985 --> 15:18.989
WHERE EVERYTHING'S ALL HALOS
AND ALL-YOU-CAN-EAT BUFFETS

15:18.989 --> 15:20.390
AND STUFF.

15:20.390 --> 15:25.956
AND, I MEAN, SHARING YOUR ORGANS
IS REALLY GREAT AND ALL.

15:25.956 --> 15:29.029
BUT I THINK YOU HAVE A FAMILY.

15:29.029 --> 15:31.001
I CAN FEEL IT.

15:31.001 --> 15:35.205
SO I THINK IT'D BE REALLY GREAT
IF YOU COULD DO ME A FAVOR

15:35.205 --> 15:39.069
AND...GET BETTER.

15:39.069 --> 15:40.510
JUST...

15:42.572 --> 15:44.644
...LIVE.

15:44.644 --> 15:49.049
SO, YOU THINK YOU CAN
GIVE THAT A SHOT, FOR ME?

16:06.196 --> 16:07.637
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

16:12.542 --> 16:13.703
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

16:13.703 --> 16:17.007
OH, NO.

16:17.007 --> 16:18.478
MEREDITH!

16:18.478 --> 16:20.480
MEREDITH.
HE'S CRASHING.

16:20.480 --> 16:23.353
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
CALL A CODE!

16:23.353 --> 16:25.455
I CAN'T -- I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO.
HE'S BRAIN-DEAD.

16:25.455 --> 16:27.617
IF HE'S BRAIN-DEAD,
YOU HAVE TO LET HIM GO.

16:27.617 --> 16:29.689
NO. IT'S ONLY BEEN 5 HOURS
AND 33 MINUTES.

16:29.689 --> 16:31.661
HE'S SUPPOSED TO GET
SIX HOURS.

16:31.661 --> 16:34.564
WE CAN'T DO ANYTHING. IT'S
NOT OUR PLACE TO MAKE THAT CALL.

16:34.564 --> 16:36.566
HE'S A PERSON.
WE'RE DOCTORS.

16:36.566 --> 16:39.469
WE SHOULD HAVE EVERY RIGHT
TO MAKE THAT CALL.

16:39.469 --> 16:43.573
WE CAN'T JUST STAND HERE
AND DO NOTHING WHILE HE DIES.

16:43.573 --> 16:46.636
HE HAS A RIGHT
TO THE NEXT 27 MINUTES.

16:50.440 --> 16:51.311
SCREW IT.

16:51.311 --> 16:53.413
I'LL GET THE DOPAMINE.
YOU GET THE BLOOD.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.415
WE'LL TRANSFUSE HIM.

17:02.322 --> 17:04.094
DO YOU FEEL ANY PAIN HERE?

17:04.094 --> 17:05.095
NO.

17:05.095 --> 17:08.398
YOU KNOW,
YOU REALLY DO HAVE...

17:08.398 --> 17:10.360
BEAUTIFUL EYELASHES.

17:10.360 --> 17:13.163
UM...THANK YOU.

17:13.163 --> 17:15.365
UH, WHAT ABOUT HERE?

17:15.365 --> 17:16.366
NO.

17:16.366 --> 17:18.438
AND NICE EYES.

17:18.438 --> 17:19.439
KIND.

17:19.439 --> 17:21.671
I LIKE A MAN
WITH KIND EYES.

17:21.671 --> 17:24.544
REALLY?
YOU THINK I HAVE KIND EYES?

17:24.544 --> 17:25.545
MMM.

17:25.545 --> 17:28.318
I MEAN, UH...
YOU CAN, UM...

17:31.351 --> 17:33.453
WHAT ARE YOU
EXAMINING ME FOR?

17:33.453 --> 17:36.326
OH, YOU KNOW,
JUST ROUTINE MEDICAL STUFF.

17:36.326 --> 17:37.627
YOU'RE DOING VERY WELL.

17:37.627 --> 17:39.729
BECAUSE I'M ENJOYING
THE VIEW.

17:42.432 --> 17:44.364
OKAY...WELL...

17:44.364 --> 17:46.336
I GOT TO GO.

17:50.540 --> 17:51.771
HE'S STABLE.

17:51.771 --> 17:54.104
FOR NOW. I HAD A RADIOLOGIST
LOOK AT HIS CHEST.

17:54.104 --> 17:55.705
HE HAS
A TRAUMATIC AORTIC INJURY.

17:55.705 --> 17:58.548
IT'S GONNA RUPTURE
AND BLEED OUT.
SO HE NEEDS SURGERY.

17:58.548 --> 18:00.610
IF HE'S GONNA REMAIN
A VIABLE ORGAN DONOR.

18:00.610 --> 18:01.811
IF HE'S GONNA LIVE.

18:01.811 --> 18:02.812
IZZIE --

18:02.812 --> 18:04.184
I'M NOT GIVING UP ON HIM.

18:04.184 --> 18:06.256
HE HAS THE SURGERY --
HE LIVES LONGER.

18:06.256 --> 18:09.319
I'M GOING TO FIND THE FAMILY.
YOU GUYS GET HIM INTO SURGERY.

18:09.319 --> 18:11.661
SHE'S VICE PRESIDENT
OF FANTASYLAND.

18:11.661 --> 18:14.424
WHO DO WE GO TO
FOR SURGERY -- BAILEY?

18:14.424 --> 18:16.596
WE NEED TO GO HIGHER
THAN BAILEY.

18:16.596 --> 18:19.499
DR. BURKE.

18:19.499 --> 18:20.830
HELLO!
OKAY.

18:22.572 --> 18:24.374
[ SIGHS ]

18:24.374 --> 18:27.137
DR. BURKE, UM,
I KNOW YOU'RE BUSY,

18:27.137 --> 18:30.280
BUT OUR JOHN DOE NEEDS
AN AORTIC REPAIR.

18:30.280 --> 18:32.282
THE GUY FROM THIS MORNING?

18:32.282 --> 18:33.813
ISN'T HE LEGALLY DEAD?

18:33.813 --> 18:36.846
WELL, YEAH --
HE'S KINDA STILL AROUND.

18:36.846 --> 18:41.221
WE GAVE HIM TWO UNITS P.R.V.C.s
AND PUT HIM ON PRESSORS.

18:41.221 --> 18:42.592
ON WHOSE ORDERS?

18:45.895 --> 18:47.557
Grey: MINE.

18:50.500 --> 18:53.433
YOU GET A BRAIN-DEAD JOHN DOE
A BLOOD TRANSFUSION

18:53.433 --> 18:54.704
WITHOUT CONSULTING ANYONE.

18:54.704 --> 18:57.207
AND NOW YOU WANT ME
TO REPAIR HIS HEART?

18:57.207 --> 18:58.468
WELL, YES.

19:01.311 --> 19:03.773
YOU DO ENJOY
CROSSING THE LINE, DON'T YOU?

19:03.773 --> 19:06.746
HE IS AN EXCELLENT CANDIDATE
FOR ORGAN DONATION.

19:06.746 --> 19:09.179
I AM A SURGEON.
I SAVE LIVES.

19:09.179 --> 19:10.750
THIS GUY IS ALREADY DEAD.

19:10.750 --> 19:12.722
NOW, THIS IS THE MEN'S ROOM.

19:12.722 --> 19:15.555
EITHER WHIP ONE OUT
OR CLOSE THE DOOR.

19:18.558 --> 19:21.291
YOU'RE ASKING MY ADVICE?
YES.

19:21.291 --> 19:22.592
NOW WHO'S CHASING?

19:22.592 --> 19:25.335
NOT FUNNY.
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

19:25.335 --> 19:28.268
OKAY.
YOU WANT TO GET AROUND BURKE?

19:28.268 --> 19:31.701
YOU GOTTA FIND A WAY
TO GET THE CHIEF INVOLVED.

19:32.942 --> 19:34.604
WHAT'D I DO?

19:34.604 --> 19:37.647
HOW CLOSE A MATCH FOR THE LIVER
IS YOUR GUY TO OUR JOHN DOE?

19:37.647 --> 19:39.609
U.N.O.S. COULDN'T FIND
A BETTER MATCH.

19:39.609 --> 19:40.610
WHY?

19:40.610 --> 19:43.553
HE'S THE CHIEF'S V.I.P.,
RIGHT?

19:43.553 --> 19:44.754
RIGHT.

19:44.754 --> 19:48.488
HOW MUCH WOULD YOU KILL TO BE
IN ON A TRANSPLANT SURGERY?

19:48.488 --> 19:50.189
YOU UNDERESTIMATE ME.

19:50.189 --> 19:52.522
I'M NOT A BABY.
I'M YOUR COLLEAGUE.

19:52.522 --> 19:54.894
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO MANIPULATE ME.

19:54.894 --> 19:58.468
IF YOU WANT SOMETHING,
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS ASK.

19:58.468 --> 20:01.501
WE WANT YOU TO GO
OVER BURKE'S HEAD, TO THE CHIEF.

20:01.501 --> 20:04.804
ASK ME SOMETHING EASIER.

20:04.804 --> 20:06.506
SIR.

20:06.506 --> 20:08.408
O'MALLEY.
HOW'S MACKIE?

20:08.408 --> 20:11.681
ACTUALLY, THAT'S WHAT
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

20:11.681 --> 20:15.315
I KINDA THINK THAT --
ME AND THE OTHER INTERNS --

20:15.315 --> 20:16.346
WE THINK --

20:16.346 --> 20:18.848
O'MALLEY,
I'M NOT GETTING ANY YOUNGER.

20:18.848 --> 20:20.550
WE FOUND MACKIE A LIVER.

20:20.550 --> 20:22.792
Meredith:
WE ARE SO GOING TO HELL.

20:22.792 --> 20:24.694
BURKE IS SENDING US
STRAIGHT TO HELL.

20:24.694 --> 20:26.696
ON AN EXPRESS TRAIN.

20:26.696 --> 20:28.398
IF IT WORKS.

20:28.398 --> 20:29.699
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:29.699 --> 20:31.801
NOTHING.
NOTHING.
NOTHING.

20:37.607 --> 20:39.409
YES!

20:42.742 --> 20:44.574
[ LAUGHS ]

20:46.245 --> 20:47.447
OH, CRAP.

20:51.851 --> 20:54.624
DR. BURKE! DR. BURKE!

20:54.624 --> 20:56.686
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

20:56.686 --> 20:58.858
Karev:
EXCELLENT WORK, SIR.

20:58.858 --> 21:00.630
EXCELLENT.

21:00.630 --> 21:01.661
FLAWLESS.

21:01.661 --> 21:03.533
IT'S A SHAME
HE'S BRAIN-DEAD.

21:03.533 --> 21:06.536
IF HE WASN'T, HE WOULD BE
ON HIS FEET IN A FEW DAYS.

21:06.536 --> 21:08.738
I'M AMAZED
AT WHAT'S GOING ON.

21:08.738 --> 21:10.700
I SERIOUSLY HATE
THAT GUY.

21:10.700 --> 21:13.473
ALEX IS VERMIN.
THAT SURGERY IS OURS.

21:13.473 --> 21:15.775
AT LEAST BURKE IS DOING
THE SURGERY.

21:15.775 --> 21:17.607
I DON'T CARE ABOUT ALEX.

21:17.607 --> 21:19.379
GEORGE, YOU DID GOOD.

21:19.379 --> 21:23.813
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO DODGE BURKE
FOR THE REST OF MY CAREER.

21:23.813 --> 21:27.917
He could kill me and make it
look like an accident.

21:30.590 --> 21:31.821
THE POLICE CALLED.

21:31.821 --> 21:34.293
THEY'VE IDENTIFIED
YOUR JOHN DOE.

21:34.293 --> 21:36.596
HIS WIFE IS ON THE WAY.

21:36.596 --> 21:37.867
[ SIGHS ]

21:37.867 --> 21:39.329
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

21:49.839 --> 21:53.683
OH, MY GOD.
[ SIGHS ]

21:53.683 --> 21:54.684
KEVIN!

21:54.684 --> 21:56.015
IT'S OKAY.

21:56.015 --> 21:57.687
OH, MY GOD!

21:57.687 --> 22:01.591
MRS. DAVIDSON,
THIS IS DR. STEVENS.

22:03.022 --> 22:06.756
NOW, IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS
AT ALL, PLEASE CALL ME.

22:16.706 --> 22:20.740
IS THERE --
IS THERE STILL A CHANCE?

22:23.012 --> 22:25.875
WE CAN HOLD OFF
TILL MORNING,

22:25.875 --> 22:28.918
BUT IF THERE'S STILL
NO CHANGE, WE'D...

22:28.918 --> 22:33.052
WE'D LIKE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT ORGAN DONATION.

22:44.664 --> 22:46.696
MACKIE?

22:46.696 --> 22:47.867
MMM.

22:47.867 --> 22:50.099
HOW ARE WE TREATING YA?

22:50.099 --> 22:52.972
OH, FINE.

22:52.972 --> 22:56.075
EXCEPT THAT BEAUTIFUL BOY
WON'T LET ME SMOKE.

22:56.075 --> 22:58.708
YOU SHOULD REPRIMAND HIM.

22:58.708 --> 23:01.751
MAKE HIM CHANGE BEDPANS.

23:01.751 --> 23:04.113
[ LAUGHS ]

23:04.113 --> 23:06.015
MACKIE.

23:06.015 --> 23:09.659
THAT BEAUTIFUL BOY
MAY HAVE FOUND YOU A LIVER.

23:22.071 --> 23:24.804
[ SOBS SOFTLY ]

23:32.782 --> 23:35.715
[ PAGER BEEPS ]

23:35.715 --> 23:38.488
GOD, I SMELL GOOD!

23:39.649 --> 23:41.020
YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?

23:41.020 --> 23:43.893
IT'S THE SMELL
OF OPEN-HEART SURGERY.

23:44.894 --> 23:45.895
[ SNIFFS ]

23:45.895 --> 23:48.598
IT'S AWESOME.
IT IS AWESOME.

23:48.598 --> 23:50.029
YOU GOTTA SMELL ME.

23:50.029 --> 23:52.562
I DON'T WANT
TO SMELL YOU.

23:52.562 --> 23:53.733
OH, YES, YOU DO.

23:53.733 --> 23:56.566
YOU HAVE GOT
TO BE KIDDING ME!

23:56.566 --> 23:59.839
OKAY, I HAVE MORE IMPORTANT
THINGS TO DEAL WITH THAN YOU.

23:59.839 --> 24:02.912
I HAVE ROOMMATES, BOY PROBLEMS,
AND FAMILY PROBLEMS.

24:02.912 --> 24:05.915
YOU WANNA ACT LIKE A LITTLE
FRAT-BOY BITCH? THAT'S FINE.

24:05.915 --> 24:09.218
YOU WANNA TAKE CREDIT FOR
YOUR SAVES AND EVERYBODY ELSE'S?

24:09.218 --> 24:11.881
THAT'S FINE, TOO.
JUST STAY OUTTA MY FACE.

24:11.881 --> 24:14.083
AND FOR THE RECORD,

24:14.083 --> 24:16.826
YOU SMELL LIKE CRAP!

24:19.859 --> 24:21.791
[ SIGHS ]

24:21.791 --> 24:23.793
SHE ATTACKED ME.

24:24.834 --> 24:25.895
MERI! MERI!

24:25.895 --> 24:27.597
MERI! MERI!

24:28.898 --> 24:31.971
YOU MIGHT WANT TO LEAVE
BEFORE I CHANGE MY MIND

24:31.971 --> 24:34.243
AND LET HER BEAT YOU
TO A PULP

24:34.243 --> 24:36.876
WITH HER TINY,
INEFFECTUAL FISTS.

24:39.849 --> 24:41.851
[ SIGHS ]

24:45.254 --> 24:47.216
WHAT?

24:47.216 --> 24:48.818
NOTHING.

24:50.820 --> 24:52.191
IT'S JUST...

24:58.728 --> 25:00.570
NOTHING.

25:09.679 --> 25:11.581
OH! THIS ONE IS
SKIN GRAFTING!

25:11.581 --> 25:14.714
SKIN GRAFTING? NO WAY!
I'VE NEVER SEEN THAT DONE.

25:14.714 --> 25:16.946
ARE THOSE
MY MOTHER'S SURGICAL TAPES?

25:16.946 --> 25:19.118
WE SHOULD WATCH
THE SKIN GRAFTING ONE FIRST.

25:19.118 --> 25:21.821
WHERE DID ALL THIS STUFF
COME FROM?

25:21.821 --> 25:25.024
OH. I UNPACKED SOME OF YOUR
MOTHER'S THINGS. I WAS UPSET.

25:25.024 --> 25:27.156
AND WHEN I'M UPSET,
I LIKE TO NEST.

25:28.858 --> 25:30.600
OOOH --
HEMIPELVECTOMY!

25:30.600 --> 25:32.962
I THINK WE SHOULD WATCH
THIS ONE FIRST.

25:32.962 --> 25:33.963
NO.

25:33.963 --> 25:36.936
WE'RE NOT WATCHING
MY MOTHER'S SURGERY TAPES.

25:36.936 --> 25:38.537
WE'RE NOT UNPACKING BOXES.

25:38.537 --> 25:40.810
WE'RE NOT
HAVING LONG CONVERSATIONS

25:40.810 --> 25:43.542
WHERE WE CELEBRATE THE MOMENTS
OF OUR LIVES.

25:43.542 --> 25:45.274
AND USE A COASTER!

25:46.175 --> 25:48.017
I ORDERED CHINESE FOOD.

25:48.017 --> 25:49.619
Grey:
I HATE CHINESE FOOD!

25:49.619 --> 25:52.652
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

25:59.859 --> 26:01.691
THEY'RE EVERYWHERE.
ALL THE TIME.

26:01.691 --> 26:04.794
IZZIE'S ALL PERKY,
AND GEORGE DOES THIS THING

26:04.794 --> 26:06.896
WHERE HE'S HELPFUL
AND CONSIDERATE.

26:06.896 --> 26:08.798
THEY SHARE FOOD
AND THEY SAY THINGS

26:08.798 --> 26:10.840
AND THEY MOVE THINGS
AND THEY BREATHE.

26:10.840 --> 26:13.202
UGH.
THEY'RE LIKE HAPPY.

26:13.202 --> 26:14.744
KICK THEM OUT.

26:14.744 --> 26:17.306
I CAN'T. THEY JUST MOVED IN.
I ASKED THEM TO MOVE IN.

26:17.306 --> 26:19.809
SO, WHAT -- YOU'RE GONNA
REPRESS EVERYTHING

26:19.809 --> 26:21.681
IN SOME
DEEP, DARK, TWISTED PLACE

26:21.681 --> 26:23.713
UNTIL ONE DAY
YOU SNAP AND KILL THEM?

26:23.713 --> 26:25.114
YEP.

26:25.114 --> 26:28.117
THIS IS WHY
WE ARE FRIENDS.

26:28.117 --> 26:31.160
WHY IS THE NAZI MAKING US STAY
IN THE PIT TWO DAYS IN A ROW?

26:31.160 --> 26:32.692
Grey: LEFTOVERS.

26:32.692 --> 26:33.693
LEFTOVERS.

26:33.693 --> 26:34.864
GOT TO GET THE CYCLISTS

26:34.864 --> 26:36.796
WHO WERE TOO DRUNK,
STUPID, OR SCARED

26:36.796 --> 26:38.267
TO GET
TO A HOSPITAL YESTERDAY.

26:38.267 --> 26:40.970
MEANWHILE, SHE GETS TO DO
A FREAKIN' ORGAN HARVEST.

26:40.970 --> 26:42.201
IT KILLS YOU,
DOESN'T IT?

26:42.201 --> 26:43.933
THAT WOMEN
CAUGHT THE HARVEST.

26:43.933 --> 26:46.375
NO, IT KILLS ME THAT ANYBODY
GOT THE HARVEST BUT ME.

26:46.375 --> 26:48.678
BOOBS DO NOT FACTOR
INTO THIS EQUATION.

26:48.678 --> 26:51.610
UNLESS, UH, YOU WANT
TO SHOW ME YOURS.

26:54.744 --> 26:56.816
I'M GONNA BECOME
A LESBIAN.
ME TOO.

26:57.887 --> 26:59.889
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

27:02.922 --> 27:05.224
NOW, MRS. DAVIDSON,
THIS FORM SIMPLY SAYS

27:05.224 --> 27:08.627
YOU CONSENT TO THE DONATION OF
YOUR HUSBAND'S MAJOR ORGANS --

27:08.627 --> 27:10.359
HEART, LUNGS, LIVER,
AND KIDNEYS.

27:12.001 --> 27:13.933
[ SIGHS ]

27:16.135 --> 27:18.067
NOW, I NEED TO ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS.

27:18.067 --> 27:19.939
ARE YOU WILLING
TO DONATE HIS CORNEAS?

27:21.941 --> 27:23.873
YOU WANT HIS EYES?

27:26.776 --> 27:31.050
UM, CORNEAL TRANSPLANTS CAN GIVE
SOMEONE BACK THEIR SIGHT.

27:34.784 --> 27:36.726
I SUPPOSE THAT'S OKAY.

27:43.963 --> 27:45.394
[ SIGHS ]

27:51.901 --> 27:53.843
WHAT ABOUT HIS SKIN?

27:55.074 --> 27:56.275
WHAT?

27:56.275 --> 27:58.277
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

27:58.277 --> 28:00.950
IT'S USED
TO HELP BURN VICTIMS.

28:02.812 --> 28:05.755
YOU WANT TO CUT OFF
HIS SKIN?

28:07.957 --> 28:11.090
WHAT ABOUT THE FUNERAL?

